ystems enforce undocumented status and perpetuate disability. At one point, in the midst of advocating for her daughter, Claudia suddenly finds herself struck by debilitating pain. Claudia is lifted up by her comadres, sent to the doctor, and reminded why she must care for herself. A braided narrative that speaks to the power of stories for creating connection, this book reveals what remains undocumented in the motherhood of Mexican women who find themselves making impossible decisions and multiple sacrifices as they build a future for their families.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aNACCS Tejas Foco Award, mothers, disability justice, testimonio, ethnography, borderlands.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107665160 cprintz978147732613840uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32612140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477326145423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477326145/original  a978-3-11-076651-6  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alle